  "prompt": "What is the best free online course for website design?",
  "response": "The \"best\" free online course for website design can vary depending on your preferences and learning style. However, some highly recommended options include:\n\n1. **Coursera \u2013 Web Design for Everybody: Basics of Web Development & Coding Specialization**:\n   - Offered by the University of Michigan, this course covers the basics of web design, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and responsive design.\n\n2. **edX \u2013 HTML5 and CSS Fundamentals**:\n   - This course, offered by W3C (the organization that develops web standards), covers the fundamental technologies needed to build web pages.\n\n3. **Codecademy \u2013 Learn HTML and Learn CSS**:\n   - These interactive courses are great for beginners and cover the basics of HTML and CSS comprehensively.\n\n4. **FreeCodeCamp \u2013 Responsive Web Design Certification**:\n   - This comprehensive program covers HTML, CSS, Flexbox, Grid, and responsive design principles through project-based learning.\n\n5. **Udemy \u2013 Web Design for Beginners: Real World Coding in HTML & CSS**:\n   - While Udemy courses typically cost money, there are often discounts, and you can find some courses for free. This is a highly-rated option for beginners.\n\n6. **Google Digital Garage \u2013 Fundamentals of Digital Marketing**:\n   - While focused on digital marketing, this course includes essential modules on web design principles.\n\nEach of these courses offers unique features and benefits, and it's advisable to explore a couple to see which aligns best with your learning style and goals.",
